	(gr_text "You can squisih everything together and make the board smaller, also bring in the left side it \ndoesnt need to be that far out\n\nSome pads are not connected to GND, run the DRC\n\nwhat are the current requirements, some traces might need to \nbe thicker if you are expecting higher current\n\nUse the schematic to help with placement, if the schematic shows a capcitor near\na specific component like a power header, then the capacitor should be\nclose to that. Right now, all the capacitors are just next to each other\nwhich is not really their purpose\n"
		(at 122.32 39.44 0)
		(layer "Edge.Cuts")
		(uuid "eef64c1c-381b-4c6a-882b-2739e5d0d3ec")
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
				(thickness 0.15)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
	)
	(gr_text "1) I would not use a plane on top, there is not really a need\n2) If something is tht and connects to a plane, it does not need a via\n3)Wrong connectors, use jst-GH\n4)C1 is just in the middle of nowhere, it should be closer to the\npower input\n5) you have a lot of space, switch smd components to 0805\n6) you can bring the jsts on the right closer in, esp when you \nswitch them for the right ones\n7) mounting holes + silkscreen pinout\n8) Make sure you double check you can use pin 43 as ADC\n9) add 22nF capactor by the ADC pin"
		(at 194.75 47.75 0)
		(layer "User.1")
		(uuid "4885a700-5424-4c2a-95d9-0bde1da0ce1d")
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
				(thickness 0.15)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
	)
